Statcast_full = sqldf("
              select a.*, b.FanGraphID, b.Team,b.TEAM_ID  
              from 
              statcast_num a,
              statcast_ID2 b
              on a.Row_Column_Ind
                      =b.Row_Column_Ind
                      ")

FDG_AD2 = FDG_AD %>% dplyr::select(-Season,-playerid,-Team)

FDG_PV2 = FDG_PV%>% dplyr::select(-Season,-playerid,-Team, -Name)

FDG_WinProb2 = FDG_WinProb %>% dplyr::select(-Season,-playerid,-Team,-Name)

Statcast_FGD = sqldf("
              select a.*, b.*, c.*,d.*
              from 
              Statcast_full a
              left join
              FDG_AD2 b,
              FDG_PV2 c,
              FDG_WinProb2 d
              on a.FanGraphID = b.FanGraphID
              and a.FanGraphID = c.FanGraphID
              and a.FanGraphID = d.FanGraphID
                      ")

Combine and Clean Team data


FDG_Team = sqldf("
    select a.*,b.*,c.*,d.*,e.*,f.*,h.*
    from FDG_T1 a
    left join FDG_T2 b,FDG_T3 c,FDG_T4 d,
    FDG_T5 e, FDG_T6 f, FDG_T7 h
                on 
                a.team = b.team 
                and a.team = c.team
                and a.team = d.team
                and a.team = e.team
                and a.team = f.team
                and a.team = h.team
                and a.Season = b.Season
                and a.Season = c.Season
                and a.Season = d.Season
                and a.Season = e.Season
                and a.Season = f.Season
                and a.Season = h.Season
                 ")

FDG_Team2 <- FDG_Team[, !duplicated(colnames(FDG_Team))] 

FDG_Team2 %>%
  group_by(Team) %>%  
summarize(sum_W = sum(W))

require(DataCombine)

Replaces <-data.frame(from = c("KCR","SDP","TBR","SFG","CHW","WSN"), to = c("KC","SD","TB","SF","CWS","WAS"))

FDG_Team3 <- DataCombine::FindReplace(data = FDG_Team2, Var = "Team", replaceData = Replaces, from = "from", to = "to", exact = TRUE)
Only exact matches will be replaced.
FDG_Team4 <- FDG_Team3 %>% rename_with( ~ paste0("T_", .x))

Final Dataset

Worth of each stat


df_final_whip1 = df_final %>%
mutate(
  WHIP = (p_walk+p_total_hits)/p_formatted_ip,
  GS = ifelse(year == 2020, 60, 162),
  win_share_IP =ifelse(p_win < 1,0, (p_win/GS)),
  save_share_IP =ifelse(p_save < 1,0, (p_save/GS)),#/p_formatted_ip)),
  hold_share_IP =ifelse(p_hold < 1,0,  (p_hold/GS)),#/p_formatted_ip)),
  SO_share_IP = ifelse(p_strikeout < 1,0,(p_strikeout/GS)),#/p_formatted_ip)),
  WHIP_share_IP = ifelse(WHIP < 0.00001,0,((WHIP))),
  ERA_share_IP = ifelse(p_era < 0.00001,0, ((p_era)))
  )

df_rank_test= df_final_whip1 %>%
#  arrange(player_id,year) %>% 
  group_by(year) %>% 
  mutate(
    win_share = order(order(rank(win_share_IP,ties.method = 'average'),decreasing = FALSE))/n(),
     save_share = order(order(rank(save_share_IP,ties.method = 'average'),decreasing = FALSE))/n(),
     hold_share = order(order(rank(hold_share_IP,ties.method = 'average'),decreasing = FALSE))/n(),
     SO_share = order(order(rank(SO_share_IP,ties.method = 'average'),decreasing = FALSE))/n(),
     WHIP_share = order(order(rank(WHIP_share_IP,ties.method = 'average'),decreasing = FALSE))/n(),
     ERA_share = order(order(rank(ERA_share_IP,ties.method = 'average'),decreasing = FALSE))/n(),
    Worth = win_share+save_share+hold_share+SO_share+WHIP_share+ERA_share
    ) %>% select (Row_Column_Ind,player_id,year,Worth) 


df_final_whipc_values =  df_final_whip1 %>%
#  arrange(player_id,year) %>% 
  group_by(year) %>% 
  mutate(
    win_share = order(order(rank(win_share_IP,ties.method = 'average'),decreasing = FALSE))/n(),
     save_share = order(order(rank(save_share_IP,ties.method = 'average'),decreasing = FALSE))/n(),
     hold_share = order(order(rank(hold_share_IP,ties.method = 'average'),decreasing = FALSE))/n(),
     SO_share = order(order(rank(SO_share_IP,ties.method = 'average'),decreasing = FALSE))/n(),
     WHIP_share = order(order(rank(WHIP_share_IP,ties.method = 'average'),decreasing = FALSE))/n(),
     ERA_share = order(order(rank(ERA_share_IP,ties.method = 'average'),decreasing = FALSE))/n(),
    Worth = win_share+save_share+hold_share+SO_share+WHIP_share+ERA_share
    ) %>% ungroup()

Checking for transformations


#Exponent to 2 really normalizes the distribution

df_final_whipd_values = df_final_whipc_values %>% 
  mutate(
    Worth = ((Worth)^(2))
    
  )

df_final_whipf_values = as.data.frame(DT)

df_final_whipf_values$WorthF = (df_final_whipf_values$Worth)^(1)

Boosted Regression Tree Model Through XGBoost


set.seed(15674)  # For reproducibility
# Create index for testing and training data
inTrain <- createDataPartition(y = df_modelfile_init2alt2021$WORTH, p = 0.80, list = FALSE)
# subset pitching data for training
tr_2021 <- df_modelfile_init2alt2021[inTrain,]
# subset the rest to test
te_2021 <- df_modelfile_init2alt2021[-inTrain,]

nrow(tr_2021)/nrow(df_modelfile_init2alt2021)
[1] 0.8
Convert the training and testing sets into DMatrixes: DMatrix is the recommended class in xgboost.

cleaning documentations: https://www.kaggle.com/pelkoja/visual-xgboost-tuning-with-caret

https://winvector.github.io/vtreat/index.html


treat_plan_2021 <- vtreat::designTreatmentsZ(
  dframe = tr_2021, # training data
  varlist = colnames(tr_2021) %>% .[. != "hitting_score1"], # input variables = all training data columns, except random
  codeRestriction = c("clean", "isBAD", "lev"), # derived variables types (drop cat_P)
  verbose = FALSE) # suppress messages

#clean stands for cleaned numerical variable, isBAD indicates that a value replacement has occurred (which indicates a missing value in this case), and lev is a binary indicator whether a particular value of that categorical variable was present.  

#### Checking Scoreframe

score_frame <- treat_plan_2021$scoreFrame %>% 
  select(varName, origName, code)

head(score_frame)


tr_treated_2021 <- vtreat::prepare(treat_plan_2021, tr_2021)
te_treated_2021 <- vtreat::prepare(treat_plan_2021, te_2021)

In addition, well be taking out a hold-out set. This is because looking at the cross-validated RMSE can give over-optimistic view on the model performance, In order not to sacrifice too much training data, well be taking an 80/20 split with dplyr:

treat_plan_2021 <- vtreat::designTreatmentsZ(
  dframe = tr_2021, # training data
  varlist = colnames(tr_2021) %>% .[. != "hitting_score1"], # input variables = all training data columns, except random
  codeRestriction = c("clean", "isBAD", "lev"), # derived variables types (drop cat_P)
  verbose = FALSE) # suppress messages

#clean stands for cleaned numerical variable, isBAD indicates that a value replacement has occurred (which indicates a missing value in this case), and lev is a binary indicator whether a particular value of that categorical variable was present.

Next, we build tuning grid for caret to explore between different hyperparameter values. To get started were using some suggestions from: https://www.slideshare.net/OwenZhang2/tips-for-data-science-competitions/14.

defaultW <- getOption("warn") 
options(warn = -1) 



# maximum number of trees
nrounds <- 1000

# note to start nrounds from 200, as smaller learning rates result in errors so
# big with lower starting points that they'll mess the scales
tune_grid <- expand.grid(
  nrounds = seq(from = 200, to = nrounds, by = 50),
  eta = c(0.025, 0.05, 0.1,0.15, 0.2,0.25, 0.3),
  max_depth = c(2, 4, 6, 8, 10,12,14,16),
  gamma = 0,
  colsample_bytree = 1,
  min_child_weight = 1,
  subsample = 1
)

tune_control <- caret::trainControl(
  method = "cv", # cross-validation
  number = 5, # with n folds 
  ## Note this was # out in the original code
  #index = createFolds(tr_treated$Id_clean), # fix the folds
  verboseIter = FALSE, # no training log
  allowParallel = TRUE # FALSE for reproducible results 
)



xgb_tune_2021 <- caret::train(
  x = input_x,
  y = input_y,
  trControl = tune_control,
  tuneGrid = tune_grid,
  method = "xgbTree",
  verbose = FALSE
  ,verbosity = 0
)

# helper function for the plots
tuneplot <- function(x, probs = .90) {
  ggplot(x) +
    coord_cartesian(ylim = c(quantile(x$results$RMSE, probs = probs), min(x$results$RMSE))) +
    theme_bw()
}

Second Tuning: Maximum Depth and Minimum Child Weight

After fixing the learning rate to 0.1 and well also set maximum depth to 3 +-1 (or +2 if max_depth == 2) to experiment a bit around the suggested best tune in previous step. Then, well fix maximum depth and minimum child weigh

tune_grid2 <- expand.grid(
  nrounds = seq(from = 50, to = nrounds, by = 50),
  eta = xgb_tune_2021$bestTune$eta,
  max_depth = ifelse(xgb_tune_2021$bestTune$max_depth == 2,
    c(xgb_tune_2021$bestTune$max_depth:4),
    xgb_tune_2021$bestTune$max_depth - 1:xgb_tune$bestTune$max_depth + 1),
  gamma = 0,
  colsample_bytree = 1,
  min_child_weight = c(1, 2, 3),
  subsample = 1
)

  x = input_x,

Fourth Tuning: Gamma

Next, we again pick the best values from previous step, and now will see whether changing the gamma has any effect on the model fit:

Fifth Tuning: Reducing the Learning Rate

Now, we have tuned the hyperparameters and can start reducing the learning rate to get to the final model:


tune_grid5 <- expand.grid(
  nrounds = seq(from = 50, to = 15000, by = 100),
   eta = c(0.005, 0.01, 0.015, 0.025,0.035, 0.05,0.75, 0.1),
  max_depth = xgb_tune2_2021$bestTune$max_depth,
  gamma = xgb_tune4_2021$bestTune$gamma,
  colsample_bytree = xgb_tune3_2021$bestTune$colsample_bytree,
  min_child_weight = xgb_tune2_2021$bestTune$min_child_weight,
  subsample = xgb_tune3_2021$bestTune$subsample
)

  lag_p_total_bases_IP=(lag_p_total_bases/lag_p_formatted_ip),
  lag_p_total_pitches_IP=(lag_p_total_pitches/lag_p_formatted_ip),
  lag_p_total_strike_IP=(lag_p_total_strike/lag_p_formatted_ip),
  lag_p_total_swinging_strike_IP=(lag_p_total_swinging_strike/lag_p_formatted_ip),
  lag_n_IP=(lag_n/lag_p_formatted_ip),
  lag_n_ff_formatted_IP=(lag_n_ff_formatted/lag_p_formatted_ip),
  lag_n_sl_formatted_IP=(lag_n_sl_formatted/lag_p_formatted_ip),
  lag_n_ch_formatted_IP=(lag_n_ch_formatted/lag_p_formatted_ip),
  lag_n_cukc_formatted_IP=(lag_n_cukc_formatted/lag_p_formatted_ip),
  lag_n_sift_formatted_IP=(lag_n_sift_formatted/lag_p_formatted_ip),
  lag_n_fc_formatted_IP=(lag_n_fc_formatted/lag_p_formatted_ip),
  lag_n_fs_formatted_IP=(lag_n_fs_formatted/lag_p_formatted_ip),
  lag_n_kn_formatted_IP=(lag_n_kn_formatted/lag_p_formatted_ip),
  lag_n_fastball_formatted_IP=(lag_n_fastball_formatted/lag_p_formatted_ip),
  lag_n_breaking_formatted_IP=(lag_n_breaking_formatted/lag_p_formatted_ip),
  lag_n_offspeed_formatted_IP=(lag_n_offspeed_formatted/lag_p_formatted_ip),
  lag_RAR_IP=(lag_RAR/lag_p_formatted_ip),
  lag_WAR_IP=(lag_WAR/lag_p_formatted_ip),
  lag_Pulls_IP=(lag_Pulls/lag_p_formatted_ip),
  lag_Clutch_IP=(lag_Clutch/lag_p_formatted_ip),
  lag_SD_IP=(lag_SD/lag_p_formatted_ip),
  lag_MD_IP=(lag_MD/lag_p_formatted_ip),
  #woba Lag calc
  lag_woba=(((lag_p_walk-lag_p_intent_walk)*0.690) + (0.722*lag_p_hit_by_pitch) +(0.89*lag_p_single)+(1.27*lag_p_double)+(1.69*lag_p_triple)+(2.1*lag_p_home_run) )/(lag_p_ab+lag_p_walk - lag_p_intent_walk + lag_p_sac_fly + lag_p_hit_by_pitch)
#Removing excess variables
) %>% 
  mutate(
    p_total_swinging_strike_IP = p_total_swinging_strike/p_formatted_ip,
    p_game_finished_IP = p_game_finished/p_formatted_ip,
   T_HR_slash_9 = 1, #df_final_whipi_values[['T_HR/9']],

   ) #%>%
